<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-13T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.2325/15c: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>)<note n="31" xml:id="d408fn31">The
                                same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, on the same date to
                                the Ambassador in Peru, as telegram No. 57.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-13T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 13,
                                        1928—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>47. Please present my compliments to the President and Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs and express to them the gratification I feel. I am sure
                            their action will be for the best interest of Chile and be considered by
                            all the world as a high-minded and honorable step.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>